Walter C. Barber was named president and chief executive officer, effective Nov. 1.
Mr. Barber, 48 years old, succeeds Paul J. Sanders, 47, who retired.
Mr. Barber is currently vice president of environmental management and administration at Chemical Waste Management Inc., based in Oakbrook, Ill.
Groundwater specializes in cleaning up soil and water contaminated by leaking petroleum-products tanks. 

